App purpose: A multi-tenant web-based platform that streamlines the process of collecting, managing, and tracking product compliance information between companies and their suppliers.

![CleanShot 2025-03-19 at 12.53.47.png](attachment:e070d2e1-20ba-4d1e-a969-d433efb88ec2:CleanShot_2025-03-19_at_12.53.47.png)

![image.png](attachment:97a38c60-271b-4f31-aa28-318ed4d1e872:image.png)

We start with a question bank, which includes all the questions that could be asked for a given industry. So for example, the chemicals industry would have all the questions that chemicals industry suppliers need to report to their customers and to authorities. And each of those questions is tagged with one or more tags. So in this instance, the blue could be REACH, the red could be US EPA, etc. And when a manufacturer or a regulatory body or anyone wants to send a request for information about a given chemical product, they select the tag that contains the questions that they need to ask. So if they need to ask questions for reach, they'd select the blue tag in this case. And then they send that to the supplier company, who is notified via email that there is a product sheet request by [requesting company name] for [supplier companyâ€™s product name]. The supplier then fills out those filtered questions, those tagged questions. And when it's finished filling them out, it submits them back to the organization that sent the request in the first place, who receives an email notification indicating that there is a product sheet ready for review. And that organization then reviews it by flagging problematic answers and entering comments. And then resubmits it back to the supplier (who receives email notification) and then comments on those flags and either changes the answer or disagrees with the change. And this iterative review process goes back and forth until the requesting organization has approved all of the answers, at which point it's incorporated back into the product sheet for that product. And there it waits until the next set of questions or updates is requested.

Please note: companies can be both suppliers and customers in the system - configure your data models accordingly

